"title": "7469: temple, Herod's",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7469: temple, herod's",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Herod's temple, familiar to Jesus Christ and his disciples and frequented by the first Christians, was destroyed by the Romans in A.D. 70.</p>\n<h2>The building of Herod the Great's temple</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:20\">JHN 2:20</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ visited the temple and taught in its courts</h2>\n<h3>He was taken there as a baby</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22\">LUK 2:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:34\">LUK 2:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:36-Luke2:38\">LUK 2:36–2:38</a></p>\n<h3>He stayed in the temple courts after his parents had returned home from the Passover Feast</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:41-Luke2:43\">LUK 2:41–2:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:46\">LUK 2:46</a></p>\n<h3>He cast out of the temple court those who used it for material profit</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:12-Matt21:13\">MAT 21:12–21:13</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:15-Mark11:17\">MRK 11:15–11:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:45-Luke19:46\">LUK 19:45–19:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:14-John2:16\">JHN 2:14–2:16</a></p>\n<h3>He taught in the temple</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:35\">MRK 12:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:41-Mark12:43\">MRK 12:41–12:43</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:1-Luke21:4\">LUK 21:1–21:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:14\">JHN 7:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:32\">JHN 7:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:45-John7:46\">JHN 7:45–7:46</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:2-John8:3\">JHN 8:2–8:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John10:22-John10:24\">JHN 10:22–10:24</a></p>\n<h3>The religious leaders challenged his authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt21:23\">MAT 21:23</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark11:27-Mark11:28\">MRK 11:27–11:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:1-Luke20:2\">LUK 20:1–20:2</a></p>\n<h3>He foretold the complete destruction of the temple buildings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:1-Matt24:2\">MAT 24:1–24:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:1-Mark13:2\">MRK 13:1–13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:5-Luke21:6\">LUK 21:5–21:6</a></p>\n<h2>The crucifixion and the temple</h2>\n<h3>One of the charges against Jesus Christ was that he had said he would destroy the temple</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:60-Matt26:61\">MAT 26:60–26:61</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The curtain of the temple was torn in two at Jesus Christ's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:51\">MAT 27:51</a></strong> <em>The curtain symbolised the barrier between God and his people caused by their sins.</em></p>\n<h2>Believers in Jerusalem met in the temple courtyards</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:46\">ACT 2:46</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:12\">ACT 5:12</a> <em>Solomon's Colonnade was on the east side of the temple courtyard.</em></p>\n<h2>Apostles taught and healed in the temple courtyards</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts3:1-Acts3:26\">ACT 3:1–3:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:19-Acts5:26\">ACT 5:19–5:26</a></p>\n<h2>Stephen was stoned for allegedly speaking against the temple</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:12-Acts6:14\">ACT 6:12–6:14</a><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:48-Acts7:49\">ACT 7:48–7:49</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Paul was accused of taking Gentiles into temple courtyards forbidden to them</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:27-Acts21:28\">ACT 21:27–21:28</a></p>",
